{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Wsq1138SX8BKA54RB7Hu3J","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 9)\n     2→\n     3→### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — create-story (2026-03-20T08:39Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **No integration-required ACs:** All 7 ACs are cli-verifiable. Runtime observability dimension internally depends on backend, but AC tests graceful degradation path.\n     6→- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n     7→- **Risk: Infrastructure dimension underspecified.** Story 4.1 defines full Dockerfile validation, but this story needs a placeholder for infra dimension. Scoped to \"check Dockerfile existence + basic structural checks.\"\n     8→- **No UX spec for `codeharness audit` specifically.** Derived output format from existing UX prefix patterns (`[OK]`/`[FAIL]`/`[WARN]`).\n     9→\n    10→### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — dev-story (2026-03-20T08:49Z)\n    11→\n    12→- **dimensions.ts exceeded NFR9 (300-line limit)** at 428 lines initially. Compacted to 197 lines — less readable but within constraint.\n    13→- **CLI command test needed exitOverride() pattern** — Commander throws process.exit on unknown commands.\n    14→- **Transient test flake** — 2 failing test files (5 tests) passed on immediate re-run. Not related to this story.\n    15→- **Task 7.5 not verified via actual CLI invocation** — tests cover the path but no real `codeharness audit` run against initialized project.\n    16→- **Coverage not measured per-file** — tests cover all branches structurally but no coverage report generated for new files specifically.\n    17→\n    18→### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — code-review (2026-03-20T08:56Z)\n    19→\n    20→- **HIGH: audit.ts had zero test coverage for runAudit failure path** (both JSON and human output branches) — FIXED, added 2 tests\n    21→- **MEDIUM: 5 uncovered branches** in dimensions.ts and coordinator — all fixed with new tests\n    22→- **MEDIUM: formatAuditJson did pointless property copy** — simplified to direct return\n    23→- **LOW (not fixed): report.ts dead-code fallback `?? '[WARN]'`** — impossible to reach with typed DimensionStatus\n    24→- **LOW (not fixed): readdirSafe uses `as string[]` cast** — fragile if someone adds withFileTypes option\n    25→- **Architecture: checkVerification hardcodes sprint-status.yaml path** — should be configurable but not blocking\n    26→- **Coverage: 96.71% overall, all 116 files above 80% floor, 2779 tests pass**\n    27→\n    28→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7d35892-2784-4ef1-a930-65ceb87c24e0","uuid":"182d3d1e-c69f-4b1b-bc0d-b7ec72920cd8","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:03:05.646Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 9)\n\n### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — create-story (2026-03-20T08:39Z)\n\n- **No integration-required ACs:** All 7 ACs are cli-verifiable. Runtime observability dimension internally depends on backend, but AC tests graceful degradation path.\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n- **Risk: Infrastructure dimension underspecified.** Story 4.1 defines full Dockerfile validation, but this story needs a placeholder for infra dimension. Scoped to \"check Dockerfile existence + basic structural checks.\"\n- **No UX spec for `codeharness audit` specifically.** Derived output format from existing UX prefix patterns (`[OK]`/`[FAIL]`/`[WARN]`).\n\n### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — dev-story (2026-03-20T08:49Z)\n\n- **dimensions.ts exceeded NFR9 (300-line limit)** at 428 lines initially. Compacted to 197 lines — less readable but within constraint.\n- **CLI command test needed exitOverride() pattern** — Commander throws process.exit on unknown commands.\n- **Transient test flake** — 2 failing test files (5 tests) passed on immediate re-run. Not related to this story.\n- **Task 7.5 not verified via actual CLI invocation** — tests cover the path but no real `codeharness audit` run against initialized project.\n- **Coverage not measured per-file** — tests cover all branches structurally but no coverage report generated for new files specifically.\n\n### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — code-review (2026-03-20T08:56Z)\n\n- **HIGH: audit.ts had zero test coverage for runAudit failure path** (both JSON and human output branches) — FIXED, added 2 tests\n- **MEDIUM: 5 uncovered branches** in dimensions.ts and coordinator — all fixed with new tests\n- **MEDIUM: formatAuditJson did pointless property copy** — simplified to direct return\n- **LOW (not fixed): report.ts dead-code fallback `?? '[WARN]'`** — impossible to reach with typed DimensionStatus\n- **LOW (not fixed): readdirSafe uses `as string[]` cast** — fragile if someone adds withFileTypes option\n- **Architecture: checkVerification hardcodes sprint-status.yaml path** — should be configurable but not blocking\n- **Coverage: 96.71% overall, all 116 files above 80% floor, 2779 tests pass**\n\n","numLines":28,"startLine":1,"totalLines":28}}}
